+\subsection{Parity validation}
+
+The dedicated \code{AOM_lib} implementation was validated against the
+reference Python AOM\_v0 calculations on BEER, CORN and ALPINE under three
+split/selection regimes: kfold5, kfold5+oneSE and spxy5.  The local validation
+commands \code{cpp/build/test_operators},
+\code{cpp/build/test_parity_kfold cpp/tests/reference} and
+\code{python/tests/test_parity.py} passed.  Across the nine parity cases, the
+largest reported coefficient difference was below $10^{-8}$, with prediction
+and RMSE-curve differences also below the tolerance used by the parity tests.
